None of the routing/state-interaction flows are covered. These are where real regressions are most likely.

| Page | Untested flow |
|---|---|
| `App` | unknown route redirects to `/`; `document.documentElement.dataset.theme` syncs with `prefs.appTheme` |
| `Reader` | invalid `bookId`/NaN chapter → redirect to `/`; missing chapter file renders the "still being distilled" state; **autoplay chain**: finishing a chapter's TTS marks it read and auto-navigates+auto-plays the next chapter only if it has a file; keyboard `←`/`→` respect `hasChapterFile`; **`Escape` has dual behavior** — closes settings panel if open, else navigates to the book map (untested branch); scroll-progress guard when content height ≤ viewport (`pct = 100`) |
| `BookMap` | unknown book redirects; `nextBook` link only renders when a sibling with `syllabusOrder + 1` exists; "Map was enough" toggles progress; TTS "Listen" completion marks the map read |
| `Library` | search input filters `track` sections into a flat match list; `/` shortcut focuses search unless another input is focused; empty-library state when `books.length === 0`; `ContinueStrip` hides once `pct >= 100` or with no progress at all; category sections with zero books are skipped |

